<HEADLINE> Rangers 8, Orioles 7  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- David Segui hit a go-ahead, three-run
homer that capped a six-run sixth inning Thursday night as the
Texas Rangers rallied to beat the Baltimore Orioles 8-7.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Lamb had three doubles and Frank Catalanotto had three hits
for the Rangers (21-20), who have won four straight and seven of
nine, putting themselves over .500 for the first time since April
