<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-19 02:55 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Hawks To Name Suhonen Coach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TORONTO (AP) -- Toronto Maple Leafs assistant Alpo Suhonen will
be named the new head coach of the Chicago Blackhawks on Monday,
the Toronto Star reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Sources close to both the Maple Leafs and Blackhawks said
Suhonen has already agreed to terms with Chicago, the Star said.
</P>
<P>
   Suhonen, from Finland, would become the first European-born and
trained head coach in NHL history.
</P>
<P>
   ''All that's left is the announcement,'' a source close to the
situation told the Star.
</P>
<P>
   Suhonen interviewed for the job on Sunday in Martha's Vineyard,
Mass., at the home of Blackhawks director of hockey operations Mike
Smith. He also spent Monday and Tuesday in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   That Smith would be the first to hire a European head coach and
employ Suhonen is not a surprise. The former associate GM of the
Leafs has long been an admirer of European players and was
instrumental in Suhonen's career as a head coach in the minor
leagues and an assistant in the NHL.
</P>
<P>
   Suhonen might not be the only European head coach in the NHL
next season. Ivan Hlinka of the Czech Republic is expected to be
named to the same position with the Pittsburgh Penguins.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
