Two Bombs Explode in Estonia Store
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   TALLINN, Estonia (AP) -- Two bombs exploded today in a department store in
the center of Estonia's capital, injuring four people, police said. The first
bomb went off at 4:45 a.m., some time after an unidentified man speaking Russian
phoned security officials at the Stockmann store, saying there was a bomb in the
building and threatening to set it off if he did not receive $114,000, the
Baltic News Service reported, citing emergency officials. Nobody was injured in
that blast, but a second bomb went off about six hours later in the same
department, injuring four people, security police spokesman Hannes Kont said.
