<HEADLINE> Madonna's British Boyfriend Arrested  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Madonna's boyfriend was arrested and charged with
allegedly attacking a man outside the pregnant star's London home,
a British news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Film director Guy Ritchie, 31, was charged with assault causing
actual bodily harm and was released on bail, said Press
Association, the British news agency. An initial court hearing was
scheduled for June 1.
</P>
<P>
   Press Association said that Ritchie allegedly attacked a
20-year-old man after returning with Madonna from a night out at 1
a.m. Wednesday. The news agency said the man had been waiting
outside the couple's home in Kensington, an upscale west London
neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
   Scotland Yard confirmed that a man was arrested but refused to
release his name. A police spokeswoman, speaking on condition of
anonymity, said the victim -- also not identified -- suffered minor
injuries and did not require hospital treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Madonna, 41, and Ritchie, who directed the British hit ''Lock,
Stock and Two Smoking Barrels,'' announced in March that they were
expecting a child. The couple said the baby was due at the end of
the year.
</P>
<P>
   The pair met two years ago at a luncheon given by Sting's wife,
Trudie Styler. Their romance was rekindled when the singer returned
to London last fall.
</P>
<P>
   Madonna, who divorced actor Sean Penn in 1989, has a 3-year-old
daughter, Lourdes, from her relationship with Carlos Leon.
</P>
</TEXT>
