<HEADLINE> N. Korean Circus To Perform in South  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- A 70-member North Korean circus troupe
will perform in South Korea in early June to celebrate a
forthcoming summit of the two Koreas, organizers said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The Pyongyang Circus Troupe will arrive in Seoul on May 29 for a
series of performances at Seoul's Chamsil Stadium, said the
Hankyoreh Shinmun newspaper, representing the organizers.
</P>
<P>
   North Korean visits to South Korea are rare.
</P>
<P>
   The performance will come days before the first-ever inter-Korea
summit, which is scheduled in the North's capital of Pyongyang on
June 12-14.
</P>
<P>
   It will be the second North Korean performance in South Korea
ahead of the summit. A 100-member North Korean boys' arts troupe is
scheduled to perform in Seoul on May 24-26.
