<SUBHEAD>
McGwire Hits 539th Home Run
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark McGwire broke ties with Mickey Mantle and Willie
Mays, homering three times and setting a career high with seven RBIs last night
in the St. Louis Cardinals' 7-2 win over the Philadelphia Phillies. McGwire is
eighth on the career list with 539 homers, three ahead of Mantle. McGwire's 64th
multihomer game broke a tie with Mays for the second-most ever. Babe Ruth had
72. McGwire broke a tie with Mantle in the first inning when he hit a three-run
drive off Curt Schilling. McGwire hit a two-run homer in the second inning, then
added a two-run shot in the eighth off Wayne Gomes for No. 539.
AP NewsBrief by DAVID GOODMAN 
</P>
