<HEADLINE> Dow Sinks 77; Nasdaq Drops 52  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 77
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 5-2 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 52 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down 13 points.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks are facing renewed pressure on the interest rate front.
</P>
<P>
   With little else to drive the markets, analysts say investors
are thinking about the impact that higher rates would have on
corporate earnings and stock prices.
</P>
<P>
   Yesterday, that left the Nasdaq-composite with a triple-digit
loss. That decline carried over to foreign markets today.
</P>
<P>
   And Wall Street is getting hit with the downward momentum again
early today.
</P>
<P>
   Also, there's stronger-than-normal trading volume on the NYSE,
tied to today's double-witching expiration of certain stock and
index options.
</P>
