<HEADLINE> Sen. Thurmond Hospitalized Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- For the third time in recent days, South
Carolina Sen. Strom Thurmond has been hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
   The Republican senator was taken to Walter Reed Army Medical
Center around 2 a.m. Friday after he apparently threw his back out,
said spokeswoman Genevieve Erny.
</P>
<P>
   ''The doctors have decided he should remain in the hospital,''
Erny said. ''We do not know when he will be released.''
</P>
<P>
   Thurmond, who at 97 is the oldest senator in American history,
is on bed rest and pain medication.
</P>
<P>
   He has suffered from lower back problems for a number of years,
Erny said.
</P>
<P>
   The senator was released from Walter Reed Monday after twice
being hospitalized for an upset stomach and fatigue.
</P>
</TEXT>
