<HEADLINE> Gores Celebrate Anniversary in Del.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Vice President Al Gore and his wife, Tipper,
slipped out of town by Marine helicopter on Friday to celebrate
their 30th wedding anniversary at the Delaware shore.
</P>
<P>
   Aides said the couple -- with a Secret Service detail, a military
aide and press aide in tow -- were borrowing the beach home of
campaign chairman Tony Coelho and would return to Washington on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The Democratic presidential candidate recently promised campaign
reporters, apparently without consulting his wife, that they could
accompany him on vacation travels in a small press pool. White
House aides notified reporters of the trip Friday afternoon -- after
the Gores were en route to the coast -- and invited them to the
area.
</P>
