<HEADLINE> Philippine Floods Kill At Least 10  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MANILA, Philippines (AP) -- Floods in the northern Philippines
triggered by days of heavy rain killed at least 10 people and left
one person missing, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The tropical storm that dumped torrential rains over wide areas
of the northern Philippines was reported gaining strength as it
moved toward southern Japan.
</P>
<P>
   Rains, however, was expected to continue in the Philippines
until Sunday, the Office of Civil Defense said.
</P>
<P>
   It said floodwaters had receded in most of metropolitan Manila
and in the several provinces.
</P>
<P>
   The number of people evacuated had fallen considerably. At the
height of the rains and floods, about 112,000 people were forced to
flee their homes to escape rising floodwaters.
</P>
<P>
   Six people drowned, three others were killed by collapsing
structures and another person died of electrocution, the civil
defense office said.
</P>
<P>
   The floods came at the start of the rainy season in the
Philippines. As many as 20 typhoons and tropical storms pass
through the country annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
