<HEADLINE> Clinton Approves Aid for UN Mission  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton authorized the Defense
Department Friday to provide up to $20 million in military goods
and support services to aid United Nations efforts in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
   ''We will do what is necessary for Sierra Leone so the
international community can get the job done,'' Clinton said in a
statement issued by the White House. ''We have a genuine
opportunity to make a difference, to give them a chance for a
better future, and to aid the cause of stability and democracy in
Africa. ''
</P>
<P>
   This assistance will include military transport, supplies,
equipment and services.
</P>
