<HEADLINE> Maradona Back on Soccer Field  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HAVANA (AP) -- Diego Maradona, briefly, was back on a soccer
field, scoring goals.
</P>
<P>
   With little defense and no goalkeeper to contend with, it wasn't
much of a test of Maradona's skills. But the former superstar did
tally four times in a friendly, half-hour game Friday night against
University of Havana soccer players.
</P>
<P>
   Maradona didn't even bother to lace up his cleats for the match
in Havana's Marianao neighborhood.
</P>
<P>
   Visibly overweight and sweating heavily in a jersey from
Argentine club Boca Juniors, Maradona played with five teammates,
including his manager, Guillermo Coppola. They won 4-2.
</P>
<P>
   Maradona arrived in Cuba in January to be treated for a heart
condition and the cocaine use that caused it.
</P>
<P>
   His Cuban doctors have said he is fit enough to play in an
exhibition game in honor of German soccer great Lothar Matthaeus in
Munich next Friday. But they insist Maradona must return to Cuba
immediately after that game to continue his rehabilitation.
</P>
</TEXT>
