<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angels' Dickson To Go Back on DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Angels right-hander Jason Dickson will go
on the disabled list with tendinitis in his left hip and stiffness
in his pitching shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Anaheim will purchase the contract of right-hander Brett
Hinchliffe from Triple-A Edmonton and transfer right-hander Tim
Belcher from the 15-day to the 60-day DL.
</P>
<P>
   Angels general manager Bill Stoneman said the moves will be
effective Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Dickson went on the 15-day DL April 29 with a strained left hip
flexor muscle and was activated Sunday. But after his first start
back, he felt pain in his hip and stiffness in his throwing
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   He is 2-2 with a 6.11 ERA in six starts this season.
</P>
<P>
   Hinchliffe was 1-2 with a 3.24 ERA in 13 games, including one
start, for Edmonton.
</P>
<P>
   Belcher, 38, was placed on the 15-day DL in March. He is
recovering from off-season surgery on his right elbow.
</P>
</TEXT>
