<HEADLINE> Mayor Street absent during aftermath of pier collapse  </HEADLINE>
With AM-NJ--Pier Collapse Bjt
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mayor John Street was no where to be found
Friday as media gathered at the site of a collapsed pier on
Delaware Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   Street was in South Carolina, attending the medical school
graduation of his nephew, said his spokeswoman, Barbara Grant. The
mayor had assessed the situation and decided not to come back
immediately, she said.
</P>
<P>
   In his place, the mayor's Chief of Staff, Stephanie
Franklin-Suber, took center stage, fielding questions from media
Thursday night and Friday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Mayor Street may be out of town, but he has been in constant,
consistent communication,'' Franklin-Suber said later Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Street issued a statement requesting that all the piers along
the Delaware River be inspected. The nearly two dozen piers were
OK'd by city inspectors late Friday, Franklin-Suber said.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our goal, of course, will be to ensure that nothing of this
nature ever occurs again along our waterfront or anywhere else in
the city,'' Street said.
</P>
</TEXT>
